obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE SHORE NUISANCES (BOMBAY AND KOTABA) ACT, 1853`
  line `A CT N O. XI OF 185 3`
  line `[ Passed on the 1 5 th July, 185 3.]`
  line `1. Empowers the Collector, & c. to require the removal of Nuisances, &c. in the harbor, &c. and in`
  line `default to abate them himself.`
  line `2, 3, 4, Authorizes the proprietor of the Nuisance on receipt of notice from Collector to apply by`
  line `petition to Supreme Court, to stop proceedings of Collector, &c. ( 3 ) the onus probandi to lie on petitioner`
  line `to prove his alleged right: (4) petition to be presented within a month, except under special`
  line circumstances.
  line `5. Prescribes mode of proceeding in case of no petition being presented or of petition being decided`
  line `against petitioner.`
  line `7. Empowers Collector to sell materials of encroachment.`
  line `8. Save rights of E.I. Co. as trustees fo r the Crown, &c.`
  line `9. Defines the term “high water mark.”`
  line `Schedule. 1. Notice. 2. Warrant.`
  line `An Act to facilitate the removal of Nuisances and Encroachments below High - water Mark in the Islands`
  line `of Bombay and Colaba.`
  line `Whereas there is a large sea - shore in the I slands of Bombay and C olaba, and it is expedient, with a`
  line `view to the safe N avigation of the H arbour of Bombay, and to the public interests generally, to facilitate`
  line `the removal of nuisances, obstructions and enroachments below high - water mark in the said H a rbour, or`
  line `upon or about the shores of the said I slands; i t is enacted as follows: —`
  line `I. It shall be lawful for the Collector of Land R evenue at Bombay to give notice requiring the`
  line `removal of any nuisance, obstruction or encroachment anywhere below high - water mark in the said`
  line `H arbour of Bombay, or upon or about the shore of the said I slands; such notice shall be given by affixing`
  line `the same in some conspicuous place on or near to the encroachment, obstruction or nuisance complained`
  line `of, and by publication thereof in th e Bombay Government Gazette, andshall State that, unless the`
  line `nuisance, obstruction or encroachment be removed or abated within one month, the same will be removed`
  line `or abated by the said Collector;such notice may be in the Form No. 1, in the Schedule to this Act annexed,`
  line `or to the like effect.`
  line `II. If any person shall deny the right of the said Collector to effect such abatement or removal, he`
  line `shall, within one month after such notice shall have been given as aforesaid, apply to the Supreme Court`
  line `of Judicature at Bombay by petition, setting forth the grounds of his alleged right and praying that the said`
  line `Collector may be restrained f rom causing such abatement or removal; andthe said Court may thereupon`
  line `(on the petitioner ’ s giving sufficient security for costs), fix a time for hearing and adjudicating upon such`
  line `petition, and given such directions, and make such orders as the said Court may think just, and the said`
  line `Court may also make an order for restraining the alleged nuisance, obstruction or encroachment from`
  line `being extended, or from being abated or removed by the said Collector, until after adjudication upon the`
  line `said petition, or the dismissal thereof for want of prosecution.`
  line `III. Upon the hearing of every such petition, the onus of proving the alleged right shall be on the`
  line petitioner.
  line `IV. No person shall be allowed, after the expiration of such period of one month, to present any suc h`
  line `petition as aforesaid, unless on satisfactory accounting to the said Court for the delay.`
  line `V. If no such petition shall be presented within the said period of one month, or if the same be`
  line `presented and determined against the right of the petitioner, or be dismissed for want of prosecution, it`
  line `shall be lawful for the Collector to cause such abatement or removal as aforesaid, by any person or`
  line `persons to be authorized by warrant under his hand, andsuch warrant may be in the Form No. 2 in the`
  line `Schedule to this Act annexed, or to the like effect; and the said Collector, and any person acting under his`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-2
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Page 2`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  sourcePage 2
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `warrant, shall not be answerable for any damage unavoidably occasioned in the removal of any such`
  line `nuisance, obstruction or encroachment.`
  line `VI. The said Collector may s ell the materials of any encroachment or obstruction removed under this`
  line `Act, and may apply the proceeds of sale in or towards payment of the expenses of the removal, and, if any`
  line `surplus shall remain, the same be forfeited, and be paid and applied in such m anner as the Governor of`
  line `Bombay in Council shall direct.`
  line `VII. Nothing in this Act shall prejudice or affect the rights of the East India Company as trustees for`
  line `the Crown in any part of the said H arbour, or of the sea - shore of the said I slands, or preclude or interfere`
  line `with any such proceedings, civil or criminal, for abating such nuisances and encroachments as aforesaid,`
  line `as might have been had if this Act had not been passed.`
  line `VIII. The words “high - water mark” in this Act shall mean the ordinary line of high - water at monsoon`
  line tides.
  line ________
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
